---
const dashboardFeatures = [
  'How many months of expenses you have saved',
  'Whether your margin is growing or shrinking',
  'Your Emergency Fund vs. Storehouse breakdown',
]
---

<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 text-center">
        Built for income that changes.
      </h2>

      <div class="mt-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto space-y-6 text-lg text-slate-600">
        <p>
          Commission. Freelance. Seasonal business. Side hustles. If your income varies, traditional budgets break immediately.
        </p>
        <p>
          Storehouse uses what we call the <span class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Joseph Principle</span> â€” store during plenty so you're ready for lean:
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Plenty/Lean Months -->
      <div class="mt-10 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="p-6 bg-storehouse-50 rounded-xl border border-storehouse-200">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-storehouse-700">
            In plenty months
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
            When you earn more than usual, Storehouse helps you see it clearly and build your margin reserve.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl border border-slate-200">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-slate-700">
            In lean months
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
            When income is lower, you draw from your reserve without guilt or panic. That's what it's there for.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Dashboard Features -->
      <div class="mt-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 text-center">
          The dashboard shows your margin health:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3">
          {dashboardFeatures.map((feature) => (
            <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <svg
                class="h-5 w-5 text-storehouse-500 flex-shrink-0"
                fill="none"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke-width="2"
                stroke="currentColor"
              >
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-slate-700">{feature}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>

        <p class="mt-10 text-xl text-center text-slate-900 font-medium">
          This isn't about predicting the future. It's about being ready for it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
